@startuml C4_Concern_Scalability
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Cross-Cutting Concern - Horizontal & Vertical Scaling

Boundary(horizontal, "Horizontal Scaling (Multi-Node)") {
    Component(node1, "YAWL Node 1", "Instance", "Active-active")
    Component(node2, "YAWL Node 2", "Instance", "Active-active")
    Component(nodeN, "YAWL Node N", "Instance", "Active-active")
    Component(load_balancer, "Load Balancer", "Routing", "Distribution")
    Component(state_replication, "StateReplication", "Sync", "Cross-node sync")
    Component(distributed_cache, "DistributedCache", "Cache", "Shared state")
}

Boundary(vertical, "Vertical Scaling (Single Node)") {
    Component(cpu_cores, "CPU Cores", "Threads", "+16 cores")
    Component(memory_scaling, "Memory Scaling", "RAM", "+32GB RAM")
    Component(virtual_thread_pool, "VirtualThreadPool", "Concurrency", "100s threads")
    Component(jvm_tuning, "JVMTuning", "GC", "G1GC optimized")
}

Boundary(stateless_pattern, "Stateless Pattern") {
    Component(external_state, "ExternalState", "DB", "All state external")
    Component(session_affinity, "SessionAffinity", "Routing", "Client ↔ node")
    Component(state_fetching, "StateFetching", "Load", "Load from DB")
}

Boundary(limits, "Scaling Limits") {
    Component(horizontal_limit, "Horizontal: 1000+ nodes", "Scale", "Limited by coordination")
    Component(vertical_limit, "Vertical: 64 cores", "Scale", "Limited by single node")
    Component(optimal, "Optimal: Hybrid", "Balance", "100 nodes × 16 cores")
}

horizontal --> load_balancer: Uses
node1 --> state_replication: Syncs
node2 --> state_replication: Syncs
state_replication --> distributed_cache: Updates
vertical --> cpu_cores: Increases
vertical --> virtual_thread_pool: Enables
virtual_thread_pool --> jvm_tuning: Uses
external_state --> stateless_pattern: Enables horizontal

Note as N1
Horizontal Scaling (Add nodes):
- Load balancer distributes
- State replicated across nodes
- All nodes active-active
- Scales to 1000+ nodes

Vertical Scaling (More CPU/RAM):
- More cores → more virtual threads
- JVM GC tuning critical
- Per-node limit ~64 cores

Hybrid Approach:
- 100 nodes × 16 cores each
- Best of both worlds
- Elastic cloud deployment
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
